{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"31019963-038d-4f25-84c7-804aa8a9c10b","content":"This is a well-known MTP behavioral difference. **Exit code 8 means \"no tests discovered\"** — MTP treats this as a failure, whereas VSTest returned 0.\n\n**The fix:** Add `--ignore-exit-code 8` to your `dotnet test` command in CI:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test --ignore-exit-code 8\n```\n\nOr set the environment variable in your pipeline:\n\n```\nTESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8\n```\n\nBoth tell MTP to return exit code 0 when the only \"failure\" is that no tests were found. This is exactly your scenario — conditional compilation (`#if INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS`) produces zero tests when the symbol isn't defined.\n\n**Which to pick:**\n- `--ignore-exit-code 8` — explicit per-command, self-documenting.\n- Environment variable — useful if you have many `dotnet test` invocations in your pipeline.\n\nActual test failures (exit code 2) will still fail the build as expected.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"58faafb0-573f-48ab-8359-e0c12e915936","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. With MTP, when no tests are discovered (because `INCLUDE_SLOW_TESTS` is not defined), the runner returns exit code 8 (which means \"no tests found\"). VSTest used to return 0 in this case.\n\nThe fix is to set the `--ignore-exit-code` option or use the environment variable `TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE` to treat exit code 8 as success, or to configure the project to handle zero-test scenarios.\n\nLet me provide the specific fix. There are a few options:\n\n1. **`--ignore-exit-code 8`** CLI flag when running `dotnet test`\n\n\n2. **Environment variable** `TESTINGPLATFORM_EXITCODE_IGNORE=8` to ignore that exit code globally\n3. **MSBuild property** in the project file to configure how MTP handles the no-tests scenario\n\nIn MTP, exit code 0 means all tests passed while exit code 8 means no tests were found. The most practical solutions are either passing the ignore flag in the CI pipeline or setting the environment variable before running tests.\n\nI should check the migrate-vstest-to-mtp skill since it likely has specific guidance on handling this behavioral difference between the two test runners.","outputTokens":600,"requestId":"0842:307F5D:817456F:8FA91E0:69EABF2A"},"id":"7270b6e0-15f6-4094-9928-7f38fb5b0f35","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:54:15.023Z","parentId":"c9e38bdf-8d06-4ed3-9244-c45117615440"}
